# üè¶ Test Plan ‚Äì GlobalSQA Banking Web Application

## 1Ô∏è‚É£ Project Overview
The GlobalSQA Banking Web Application simulates core banking operations such as customer login, deposits, withdrawals, and transaction management.  
The goal of this testing effort is to ensure the system functions correctly, meets business requirements, and provides a smooth user experience.

---

## 2Ô∏è‚É£ Objective
- Verify that all functionalities of the banking system work as expected.
- Validate the system‚Äôs stability, usability, and performance.
- Identify and report defects before release.
- Ensure all requirements are traceable through RTM.

---

## 3Ô∏è‚É£ Scope of Testing

### ‚úÖ **In Scope**
- Functional Testing (Customer, Manager modules)
- UI and Usability Testing
- Regression Testing
- Smoke/Sanity Testing
- Cross-Browser Compatibility

### ‚ùå **Out of Scope**
- Performance and Load Testing
- Security Penetration Testing
- Backend Database Validation (since no DB access)

---

## 4Ô∏è‚É£ Test Modules
| Module Name | Description |
|--------------|-------------|
| Customer Login | Verify user login functionality |
| Manager Login | Verify manager functionalities like Add Customer, Open Account |
| Deposit | Verify deposit process and balance updates |
| Withdraw | Verify withdrawal and error handling |
| Transaction | Check transaction history displays correctly |
| Logout | Verify proper session logout |

---

## 5Ô∏è‚É£ Test Approach

| Type | Description |
|------|--------------|
| **Manual Testing** | Execute test cases manually for all modules |
| **Automation Testing** | Use Selenium WebDriver (Java/Python) for core user flows |
| **Defect Reporting** | Log defects in Bug Report Template (Bug_Report_Template.md) |
| **Test Management** | Test cases and execution tracked using Excel or Google Sheets |

---

## 6Ô∏è‚É£ Test Deliverables
- Test Plan Document  
- Test Scenarios  
- Test Cases Document  
- RTM (Requirement Traceability Matrix)  
- Bug Report  
- Test Execution Report  

---

